It is based on three sources:
1) A global monthly gridded precipitation dataset obtained from the Climatic Research Unit (University of East Anglia).


2) A GIS modeling of global Standardized Precipitation Index based on Brad Lyon (IRI, Columbia University) methodology.


3) A population grid for the year 2007, provided by LandScanTM Global Population Database (Oak Ridge, TN: Oak Ridge National Laboratory).


Unit is expected average annual population (2007 as the year of reference) exposed (inhabitants) .


This product was designed by UNEP/GRID-Europe for the Global Assessment Report on Risk Reduction (GAR). 
It was modeled using global data.


